##CHINESE STUDENTS STUDYING IN SOUTH KOREA: why I choose to return home

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wang Xin, _ the_paper _

Han yi-min (not his real name) , who studied at a university in Seoul, South Korea, stocked up on food and face masks. He planned to stay at his residence in Seoul until the end of the epidemic.

But as the epidemic spread in South Korea, Han changed her mind: On March 2, she bought a flight from Seoul to Chongqing on March 6.

On the day of his return, Han Yimin, wearing a protective suit, was taken more than five times for his temperature. After arriving in Chongqing, Han Yimin was "seamless docking" sent to the designated hotel isolation observation.

On March 10, Han told The Paper news that she had returned to the Tongnan district of Chongqing on March 8 to continue quarantine observation. In the domestic strict prevention of imported cases of the current, she will obey the management, no trouble.

Korean friends had asked her why she had returned at this time. "because our cure rate is very high and we have enforced quarantine measures, I feel very safe, " Han said

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wearing protective clothing, wearing a mask and goggles Han Yimin. All the pictures in this article are provided by the interviewees

I was struggling to get home

Han, a 25-year-old native of Tongnan County, South Korea, left for Seoul in 2017 to study at a university. According to the curriculum, she will graduate this summer. With the new outbreak of pneumonia, all bets are off.

Han yi-min returned to Chongqing for her winter vacation from Seoul on January 3 this year. She returned to Seoul on January 11 because she had something to do. A few days later, Seoul asked the Chinese, who arrived in Seoul on Jan. 13, to quarantine themselves for 14 days.

With the development of the epidemic, or to stay in Seoul, let Han Yimin tangled for a long time.

"As soon as 1,000 people are diagnosed in South Korea, I will return home immediately, " Han wrote in a message on the afternoon of Feb. 21.

On the same day, 156 new cases of coronary pneumonia were confirmed in South Korea, far from Han's "target number" . It took just four days for the number to reach 977. However, most of the confirmed cases are in the city of Daegu and the North Gyeongsang Province region.

To go to the pass, Han Yimin does not want to go.

"If I run home because I'm afraid, it's not right. If I'm in the incubation period, everyone will suffer. I'll quarantine myself in Seoul first, " Han told The Paper, she was working part time at a large shopping mall in Seoul, and worried that if she caught the disease while working part time and became an incubation period patient, she could return home and infect others, causing problems for health care workers and epidemic prevention at home.

Even if you don't get it in Seoul, you can get it on the way home. Han Yimin said: "The plane is also dangerous, we all want to run, the incubation period also want to run, space is also closed, more terrible than outside. "

On February 27, Han bought a lot of food in the refrigerator, ready to "stay at home" like ordinary people in China.

Han yi-min buys food in Seoul.

On March 1, flight CA440, carrying 57 Chinese and 22 South Korean passengers, arrived in Chongqing from Seoul. After entry quarantine, four passengers developed fever and were sent to Yubei District designated hospital in the city for further diagnosis and treatment. Fortunately, the nucleic acid test, four passengers were not infected with new coronary pneumonia.

Flight CA440 is Han's flight home every time. See afore-mentioned News, Han Yimin still is felicitous oneself did not return.

But just a day later, Han Yimin was hit in the face: as she could not buy a direct ticket, she had to choose March 6 from Beijing to return to Chongqing.

Han says it was her aunt's words that prompted her to change her mind. "Your Life is not yours alone. ". In addition, she has no national health insurance in South Korea, also do not know the new crown pneumonia in South Korea treatment procedures and costs, "think or go home more comfortable. ".

After consulting with his family, Han Yimin decided to return home. Before booking the ticket, Han Yimin's father will be ready to return to his daughter reported to the local street office and District police station.

Before departure, Han Yimin has the march rent to the landlord, the home of fresh vegetables to give away, the domestic waste disposal, the cat to settle down.

After getting off the plane, they were taken to a designated hotel for quarantine

On March 6, Han put on protective clothing, goggles and a mask. In addition to the inspection must take off goggles and masks, Han Yimin has always maintained a "fully armed. ". On the flight from Seoul to Beijing, Han filled out forms such as exit / Entry Health Declaration cards.

"As soon as I got off the plane, I felt very relieved, " Han said, adding that the anti-epidemic measures in China were in place, airport staff were wearing protective clothing and the smell of disinfectant was obvious.

Flights from Beijing to Chongqing are also strict. Han recalled that she was asked to fill out a health report when she checked in. Learn Han Yimin just returned from abroad, flight attendants will arrange her a person in the last row of the plane.

After arriving at Chongqing Jiangbei Airport, the flight attendant first arranged for other passengers to disembark, and finally arranged for Han Yimin and a Korean passenger to disembark. Both men were also temperature-checked before they left the plane.

Han said that Chongqing's prevention and control measures are also in place, from her plane to be pulled to the designated hotel observation, all the way with medical staff, police or government staff accompanied. On June 6, she was taken five to 10 times.

Han Yimin to the hotel room is 7 am, the trip did not eat much she ordered a take-away. As Han Yimin is forbidden to leave the room without authorization, the rider will take delivery to the hotel lobby, by the staff on behalf of Han Yimin to the room.

During the quarantine in Yubei District, he was ordered not to leave his room.

"The accommodation and food are good, they are free, " he said, according to a photo he sent to The Paper. The hotel offered eggs, bread, milk and porridge for breakfast, and fish, pork, cauliflower and soup for lunch.

During the observation period, Han Yimin also made a "Oolong. ". Because insert the mobile phone with domestic telephone card into mute, Han Yimin did not hear the police call to her, so Han Yimin's mother calls Wechat to ask why it does not cooperate with the police station work, why there is resistance. Han Yimin said: "I really do not resist at all, such a 'immortal' days have nothing to resist. "

After a day and a half of observation at the designated hotel, he filled out a letter of commitment and was allowed to return to Tongnan County. Meanwhile, the staff gave Han Yimin to do a nucleic acid test, the test results were negative.

Han was ordered not to return home after returning to Tongnan, and to remain in isolation at her designated hotel for another 14 days. In addition, on the way from the designated hotel in Yubei District to the designated hotel in Tongnan County, Han Yimin can not get off.

On March 9, staff gave Han a second nucleic acid test after his return, the result is still negative. Han says she will obey the management and not cause trouble to others.

Han Yimin's Korean friends had asked her why she returned to China at this time. "because we have a high cure rate and we have enforced quarantine, I feel very safe, " she said
